Created attachment 34477
Screen shot of the error at httpd.apache.org. I have screenshot of my site as well. Mine is same as attached, let me know if required.

Hi

I have CentOS 6.5 hosting with Apache 2.2.x and PHP 5.6.x. Few weeks ago, I noticed a strange error on my server which was "500 Internal Server Error" with title code # 732 in browser's tab (please see attached). 

I searched for any possible solution of error on the Internet but nothing helped. Today surprised when noticed same error at http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.2/programs/ (as you can see the attached screenshot).

The error has no logs, I checked all log files including access_log, error_log and domlogs also. Even I searched in suExec logs and all other possible log files but found nothing. 

Please take a look at this error and suggest me appropriate solution. 

Thanks
creator: manzoor.ahmed@midgr.com

text:
(In reply to Manzoor Ahmed from comment #1)
> any update on the issue?

After 90 minutes? You cannot be serious. Did your server even record a 500 error at the time?  Could be your client or a proxy.  

Bugzilla is only for reporting bugs in httpd, not for support.
